author: quintonm
msg: The isAnonymousUser() method now checks user.getUserName() instead of user.getName().  The
getName() method always returns an empty string because setName() is never called.  Since
getAnonymousUser() will call user.setUserName(""), I thought it made the most sense to change
how this method check for an anonoymous user.

author: quintonm
msg: A reference to session is no longer kept.  It will always be obtained from request.getSession().
Note: setSession() has been deprecated.  Calling it will do nothing.

author: quintonm
msg: Bugfix: formatString() should modify the string is url.case.folding is NOT set to none.
